The last days of the shelter

At the time of my last article on the 19th, seven days after I went into the shelter, I had already done two rounds of nucleic acid, the first was negative and the second was still pending.

To learn more about life in the shelter, Click:
What's the shelter like? How's life? A multi-perspective view of life in the shelter of Tazi Lake

Discharge criteria according to the shelter patient manual

The patient's condition improved after treatment and the following conditions were met:

(1) body temperature not exceeding 37 degrees for more than 3 consecutive days.

(2) respiratory symptoms (e.g. cough, chest tightness, etc.) significantly reduced or disappeared.

Chest x-ray (chest x-ray or chest CT) showed a marked improvement over the previous examination.

(D) two consecutive throat swabs (at least 1 day apart) were normal (COVID-19 was negative) .

I just need a nucleic acid test and a C.T.

On the 22nd, the doctor told me to get a CT, and the temporary CT room is outside, to the left from the tent we came in to sign in.

Queue registration.

CT, outside the room

After a while, it was my turn. After lying on the bed, I was waiting for the sound to tell me to "breathe in ~ hold it in ~ " . However, there was no sound. I pricked up my ears and kept searching. I was afraid that I would not hear and would have to do it again. I was very nervous.

And then it's done...

I came down and asked the doctor. The doctor said there's no need to hold your breath...

Inside the shelter, it's still alive.

The line of square dancers finally formed, attracting talent along the way, and in a few moments, the line expanded easily from one to two.

Mister, I just want to call you like crazy

Qigong? Taijiquan? Baduanjin?

Hello, little one

Cleaning brother's equipment has also been upgraded, from the beginning of the two-handed drag is now a car family.

Shelving, shelving.

Soldiers of the fair maiden made a video message to the people back home to say they were safe.

Remember the old man in the middle of the picture reading the book in the last Article?

He has read that one and moved on to the next

Excuse me, do doctors and nurses in Zhangjiakou have double degrees in medicine and fine arts? After the last hot dry noodles for the soul, let's continue to bring out the old and bring out the new.

My 76-year-old mother-in-law in the area, she does push-ups every morning, and I'm both impressed and concerned.

After I left, I heard from my friends in the shelter that there were runway shows and Karaoke competitions.

On the afternoon of the 22nd, people were leaving the hospital to go to the quarantine point of the school. I didn't expect that. The next day, I suddenly joined the group and was taken by surprise.


A sudden separation

Previously, patients who met the standard for discharge were sent straight home. On the 22nd, the government issued a new policy, requiring all discharged patients to be placed in a centralized quarantine for another 14 days before returning home.

I very much agree, for this virus is still a lot of things are unknown, will be infected with patients gradually reduce the level of quarantine, for their own family is good.

23rd, 10:00 a.m.

The doctor who came to my rounds told me that my second nucleic acid test came back negative, and that the CT results I had yesterday needed to be reported to a team of specialists for evaluation and absorption before I could decide whether or not to leave the hospital.

That afternoon, a nurse in Hebei, who was in charge of my area, ran to my bedside and asked me if I was the author of the article about the shelter.

After receiving my positive answer, he told me with great pleasure,

"The girls from the village are here. The nurses from Hebei will take good care of you. Don't be sad. Don't be sad. You can see we are talking with curly. "

Like a string of beans, I did not realize at that time, she smiled.

Next thing I knew, she was the one who had left me a note backstage after my last post.

A warm feeling came over me.

And then an hour later, it was her.

Came up to my bed and said, congratulations, you're getting out of the hospital today. Get your stuff

Calm tone of voice does not seem to have joy, is because I did not so did not hear out? Or did she not? Or are we not.

Surprised, I began to slowly sort through my things. A nurse came over and said the car was waiting outside. She told me to hurry up and leave.

The big sisters around knew that I was leaving the hospital right now, and they all came over to help me clean up. They were also worried that the new isolation point I was going to was not in a good environment. There was no quilt, no basin, no thermos, so they found a big bag, i put all this stuff in the shelter, and my things were packed up quickly, and they carried me to the car.

It all happened so fast, I didn't have time to think about anything, I didn't have time to have any emotions, from the time I got the call, to 15 minutes later, I was sitting on the bus to the quarantine school, my mind was blank.

In fact, this should be a happy thing, I am really good in the medical sense, I should once again announced that I beat the virus.

And yet, I couldn't be happier.

I. . . Haven't said good-bye.

It never occurred to me that this experience in the shelter would bring me so much.

This morning a nurse friend in Tianjin was telling me on Wechat that she was on night shift and would come downstairs to see me, and they had already made an appointment with me. I had to come out to see me off and take a photo with me.

And now I'm in the car that's leaving.

I sat for a long, long time, numb brush the wechat message.

Click on her profile picture and look at the input field.

For a long time, to pretend nothing like, with a tone of complaint, with Emoji, isolated my emotions, tell her I left.

She told me not to be sad,

She replied to me, waiting for the country, waiting for me to play in Tianjin, take me to eat Tianjin food, take me to listen to cross talk, take me to go to the Fifth Avenue..

She replied, "the shelter is not quiet, and washing is not convenient. ".

I saw her reply at that time, but the delay can not continue to respond, I dare not touch, I am afraid of my emotional embankment, this collapse.

I'm... still in the car.

Further information sent, forgive me for not giving you a timely response.

I turned off my cell phone and wept silently.

Another friend, whom I met in the shelter because of my last article, I didn't have the courage to tell him, even though we hadn't spent much time together.

I know there's a lot of traffic right now, and I know we can text and call whenever we want.

But sometimes, it's not so much the events themselves that we can't accept, it's the emotions they carry that weigh us down.

And now, the unfinished farewell, let the sad mood first fly for a while.


Back to school

About an hour later, the bus arrived at Wuhan Instrument Electronics School, the East campus of Changjiang Vocational College.

Patients discharged from each ward are placed in a central isolation point by the districts themselves, which is where they are discharged from Jiang'an District.

After a long wait in line, I finally arrived at the gate of the quarantined dormitory at 8 pm.

In order to avoid registration when the crowd gathered, everyone got off the queue up, 555 to enter the registration information.

First floor access to the living supplies of the boxes arranged in turn, toothbrush, toothpaste, towels, sandals and slippers, roll paper, self-collection.

Dormitory is a separate room, with a bathroom, there is hot water.

The room has a mattress, quilt, pillow, electric heater, basin, boiling kettle, garbage bags, hand sanitizer, are new.

The door of every room is unlocked, so put a stool against it.

The bathroom in the room

What you need to know

I can finally take a shower.

The next day, an enthusiastic young man organized everyone to start a group. Any news would be convenient to inform the group.

This group name is still quite a struggle to determine.

At first he called the group of patients, everyone shouted, feel wrong, and then changed to the group of patients, more against that we have been good.

And then he changed it to social group, which I thought sounded weird, so I figured I'd just go back to school.

Finally, we returned to the campus group so settled down.

We all just arrived here the night before, the building number is also silly, from 11 to 19 to 16, now look at this picture only to find that it has been changed to 19...

A group of people are standing in the hallway chatting enthusiastically for a group name.

Go back to my room.

I here is a six-person dormitory, with a balcony, downstairs is an old driving school, and then out is Guanbao highway, the front view open, I like.

The guy next door reminds me to stand in the middle of the room and turn on my phone's compass.

Wow ~ originally I live is a north-south transparent, independent bathroom with a balcony, the view of the road without blocking room wow ~ ! That's pretty impressive

Towel as a mop, squatting on the ground to polish the floor ~ at home have not done so ~ 

Maybe because we're both discharged patients, we're allowed to leave our rooms here, in the hallway, but not out of the building.

Dormitory corridor, most of the time is quiet, everyone in their own rooms.

Originally just want to see around the situation to go back to the room, dormitory inside each place is the same, also really nothing good to reach.

The result is inadvertently, I found the wonderful paste on the dormitory door, the original school is Hidden Dragon Crouching Tiger Place.

Down on the first floor, nurses are on duty 24 hours a day, taking body temperature and dispensing traditional Chinese medicine.

Listen to their introduction, they are from Wuhan Hongji Orthopaedic Hospital.

The night after I arrived, a worker arrived to install the Wi fi, working from 8 pm to 12 pm.

However, the signal in my room is not very good, but in the door is not bad, just put a stool against the door, so the daily show as follows, Oh, no, the daily study.

At first it was understaffed, with meals delivered late every day, and now it's getting better.

Two meat and two vegetables, fruit and yogurt every day, in this case, already can.

But no contrast, no harm.

After all, we are the people who have been doted on by my Tazi Lake Cabin GRANDPA. We can live in luxury and live in luxury, but we can not live in luxury.

Oh, I miss my steerage.

But, happily, it also gave me a free place in my stomach to kill off the big bag of snacks I took with me when I left home. After all, Grandpa never gave me that chance.

Breathing the fresh air, looking at the distant scenery, the leisurely afternoon tea opens.

All that plant dust, Trans Fats, high GI, no sugar, now all I want is my Yosemite, oh, no, it's Antler Alley.

Although the campus dormitory environment is not as good as the hotel and the shelter environment, but it does not prevent us to entertain ourselves, right?

Dong! I heard something land softly.


It's at the end

We're all part of the fight, but... we're all part of the fight.

With the continued support of medical teams and supplies across the country, the Wuhan outbreak is much better than it was at the beginning.

Patients are no longer hard to find, nucleic acid testing is no longer out of the door, the classification of medical treatment and order is increasingly clear.

And when we deal with the biggest crisis of our reality, when the environment around us seems less fearful, uncertain and uncertain, suddenly there is room for the individual to feel his or her own heart.

In this epidemic,

There are people who have been confined to their homes for days,

There are volunteers who have been running around,

Community workers with Battle of Julu,

There are medical personnel who have been supporting the front line all along,

There are reporters who bring us various reports from the front, but who are also in the front,

There are the police, the sanitation workers, the supermarket workers, the delivery boys, who are also on the front lines in order to keep the current social life going,

More people in Wuhan, who are in a foreign land but have been extremely worried about their hometown in their hearts,

And Ten million infected people and their families.

In the midst of an epidemic, each person has his own personal experience, something he has to face, light or heavy.

When everything around us has calmed down, when we are no longer in such a hurry and busy, when the tension is down, when there are not so many urgent moments to arouse our emotions.

The sense of experience for oneself, will sweep in.

Numbness, sadness, exhaustion, guilt, powerlessness, anger, confusion about the future, or one or more, are intertwined and spread inadvertently.

It's... It's all normal.

Waiting is a long time, in a long hold, to take your eyes back to the present moment, what I have been doing before, what I am doing now, what I can do.

It doesn't matter how small it is.

It will take time for the epidemic to end, for society to function properly, and even more for our own minds.

After the wind and snow, our love of Wuhan, will still be as warm as ever.
